Turns out the lady mentioned to another coworker who waltz in when I was paying that there were Two cooks in the back. Seriously ? As I’m paying she gives me the merchant copy tells me it’s mine/ tells me to sign it/ has my copy in the other hand, I sign hers because I know which is which and holds onto mine while going back into the kitchen to talk with the cook Let me get back to the food The steak burrito had everything it was a great size of food but alas still disappointed in texture and flavor overall. The wife is picky but if it had been anyone who might’ve been deadly allergic to onions I hope to god this lady does her job better for someone else.  The only positive thing of the quesadilla might’ve been the dough seemed freshly made or cooked. I had planned on taking some of it home yet she only bothered to bring us on dusty styrofoam container for only her meal. I had high hopes for what people raved about this place and the fact it has such a high reviews, it’s a small grease trap. Call your food in  the service was terrible. I was working at a Habitat for humanity jobsite about a mile away, and had a decision to make. Did I want to eat Burger King, which I know to be awful and cost about $10, or take a chance on one of the many (MANY) tiny taquerias in Elgin for about the same price. Here I am, so you know which way the coin flip went!  I'm glad I opted local on this one :) Taqueria El Cokito is fun, a cute little local place. I went at lunch hour on a Saturday, and it was *packed*! I'll say, I was the only guy speaking English inside - my Spanish is OK, so I'm comfy with that, but that's what the dining experience is like. Everyone was friendly and service was quick!  Food was great - for $7-8, I got 3 steak tacos with all the fixings, chips, and a jumbo horchata (if you've never had horchata, have horchata and thank me later!). Better than I expected. I was building a house, so super hungry, and the meal did not disappoint.  Admittedly, this will probably not be the best Mexican meal you've had in your life. The salsas were house-made, but didn't really pop for me. This may well be the best meal under 10 dollars you've had in a while, though! :)
